covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC06, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC23, @TC25, @TC26, @TC27, @TC28, @TC29, @TC43, @TC44, @TC45, @TC46, @TC47, @TC48, @TC49, @TC50 cover valid request handling with various parameters and edge cases.
Empty Response: @TC08 and @TC09 cover cases with no accounts or offset beyond data.
Query Parameters: Multiple scenarios test with different combinations of offset, limit, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit, and extra parameters.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for handling pagination with very large datasets (e.g., millions of accounts) or performance under load.
Authorization: No tests explicitly verify unauthorized access, invalid tokens, or permission issues.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios test system behavior under high request volume or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests check for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control, or cache invalidation.
recommendations: Add tests to verify pagination behavior with very large datasets and performance constraints.
Include scenarios for unauthorized access, invalid tokens, and permission checks.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Add tests to verify caching headers and cache invalidation mechanisms for GET responses.
